reviews.review_thoughts: I have struggled for a long time to find a daily SPF that I love. After trying, and loving, a number of other Skinceuticals products, I decided to give this one a try. I think I may have struck gold! The texture is thin and watery, but I squeeze a generous amount onto my fingertips and layer every morning on top of my CE Ferulic. It feels almost oily at first, but soaks in beautifully if you give it a minute. I have had no issues with my liquid foundation on top of this, no pilling or other texture concerns. The only issue I run into is having more of a sheen on my face throughout the day, but a dusting of powder is a quick fix. When camping or running around outside I'm sure I could wear this alone, but just out of habit I tend to still put foundation on top. I don't personally find that the tint is noticeable. I love to sample skincare and try new products so I'm sure I'll be testing out some more SPF products, but I'm certain that this one will always have a place in my arsenal.

That worked, but most mornings I don't really have time for that so I just started using a new cream that contained no silicates and stopped using the toner in the morning and switched just to using la roche posays thermal water spray. That worked really well and this spf really just melted into my skin without a white cast. As soon as I'm through this bottle I'm going to try out the tinted one.
